    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# Blob Detection using LoG , DoG\n",
        "\n",
        "A blob is an object of interest within an image. They can be characterizd as a bright object is an image with a dark background or vice versa. With this, we can define blob detection as a method to find objects in an image characterizd by a specific property. There are three methods that can be used to detect blobs. They are: <br/> <br/>\n",
        "    1- Laplacian of Gaussian (LoG) : which takes the laplacian of a Gaussian smoothed image\n",
        "    2- Difference of Gaussian (DoG), which takes the difference of two Gaussian smoothed images\n",
        "    3- Determinant of Hessian (DoH) : which takes the maximum value in the matrix of the determinant of Hessain\n",
        "<br/>\n",
        "\n",
        "Suppose we use the original and unprocessed image. in that case, the algorithm might have a hard time identifying the bright object in the dark background because there are varyin intensity levels in each pixel. this will result in an inaccurate and sluggish blob detection - which we do not want! this is the resason why we opted to use a binarized image for blob detections."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "u1HtF9n20Ybr"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 2,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "J-7noG9N0S4e"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from skimage.io import imread , imshow\n",
        "from skimage.feature import blob_dog , blob_log , blob_doh"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import cv2\n",
        "from google.colab.patches import cv2_imshow # Import the Colab patch\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load the image\n",
        "image = cv2.imread('house.JPG', 0)  # Load as grayscale\n",
        "\n",
        "# Apply a binary threshold to get the mask\n",
        "_, mask = cv2.threshold(image, 127, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display the mask using the Colab patch\n",
        "cv2_imshow(mask) # Use cv2_imshow instead of cv2.imshow\n",
        "cv2.waitKey(0)\n",
        "cv2.destroyAllWindows()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 352
